        <div class="section" id="about">
        <div class="content" style="margin-bottom:0;">
          <h3>About</h3>
             <p>At The Coder Factory we are building a community where people aren’t afraid to <b>challenge the norm</b>, where you're encouraged to try something new.</p>
             <p>Traditionally, technology has been left to expert programmers and nerds. It’s time to abandon these clichés and introduce a new <b>perspective.</b></p>
             <p>Hack The Media is about <b>exploring new ideas</b> in media. The global media industry is undergoing a huge transformation. While traditional media outlets struggle to monetize their offerings, new media formats are burgeoning. Vlogging, podcasting and live streaming are all growing at an unbelievable speed and we know there are many people, like <b>you</b>, with ideas that can revolutionise the market.
             </p>
             <br>
            <p class="hacker_intro"><b>Taking part in Hack The Media means being a:</b></p>
            <br>
             <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-sm-4">
                      </a><div class="ct-iconBox ct-iconBox--top ct-iconBox--bg text-center ct-u-bgWhite animated activate fadeInUp" data-fx="fadeInUp" data-time="0">
                          <div class="slime ct-iconBox-icon ct-iconBox-icon--default">
                              <i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></i>
                          </div>
                          <div class="ct-iconBox-content text-left">
                              <h4 class="ct-iconBox-title text-center ct-fw-600">Creator</h4>
                               <p class="drawer">We want more people in the world to be creating technology. We all have ideas and Hack The Media is how those ideas will become reality. We want you to push the boundaries of new media and take risks, whether it be by livestreaming your whole project or by working with people you've just met. </p>

                              <p class="drawer">We have an awesome lineup of sponsor-led tech talks and lead-up intro-level workshops that let anyone learn what it takes to change the world of media as we know it.</p>
                              <br>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="col-sm-4">
                  <div class="ct-iconBox ct-iconBox--top ct-iconBox--bg text-center ct-u-bgWhite animated activate fadeInUp" data-fx="fadeInUp" data-time="200">
                          <div class="parttime ct-iconBox-icon ct-iconBox-icon--default">
                              <i class="fa fa-user-plus"></i>
                          </div>

                          <div class="ct-iconBox-content text-center">
                              <h4>
                                  Leader
                              </h4>
                              <p>
                              <p class="drawer">At Hack The Media, everything changes. It's going to be an organized chaos. It's one week to make your ideas a reality.</p>

                              <p class="drawer">Perhaps you're a journalist working in traditional media with thoughts on how to revolutionise the industry. Maybe you're a digital artist such as a podcaster or vlogger who wants to inspire, or sees new ways to reach more people. People in the media have a huge influence and can encourage their audience to think about getting involved within the technology movement. At the center of this is you and your ideas. We take pride in helping you build connections and content.</p>
                              </p>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="col-sm-4">
                 <div class="ct-iconBox ct-iconBox--top ct-iconBox--bg text-center ct-u-bgWhite animated activate fadeInUp" data-fx="fadeInUp" data-time="400">
                          <div class="fasttrack ct-iconBox-icon ct-iconBox-icon--default">
                              <i class="fa fa-graduation-cap"></i>
                          </div>

                          <div class="ct-iconBox-content text-left">
                              <h4 class="ct-iconBox-title text-center ct-fw-600">
                                  Mentor
                              </h4>
                              <p class="drawer">No one should be afraid to ask for help.</p>

                              <p class="drawer">If you plan on working with a specific technology, we can help you find someone who knows what you need. Our mentors span across industries, television, technology, investing, blogging, and everything in between. The mentors are there to help you out.</p>

                              <p class="drawer">Throughout Hack The Media, we are encouraging everyone to use their own knowledge to help where possible. The spirit and courage to change the media allows each person to be both a mentor and a mentee. </p>
                              <br>
                              
                      </div>
